      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Some 4,800 people have received pension checks this year because they looked for their names on a Web site created by the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, the federal agency that insures traditional pensions.</p>
        <p>They will collect about $10 million in benefits, the agency said.</p>
        <p>The agency has posted on its site, www.pbgc.gov, the names of 12,000 people who participated in plans that the agency has taken over but who have not applied for pension benefits. Some of those people, the agency said, may not have qualified for benefits, but by applying they can get a final determination.</p>
        <p>David Cay Johnston</p>
        <p>PERSONAL BUSINESS: DIARY</p>
      </block>
